test19.testCaseDes: Test 19: This is a profile with a Primary member and 4 Dependents. Primary member has PHI and member 02 is an Adult Dependent who has NOT given permission to Primary. Everyone else in the plan are Child Dependents and no one has used any cleaning in a Calendar Year. This test verifies that the Primary is blocked from seeing his/her own usage information (PHI restrictions) and the Adult Dependent's usage information (Omnibus restrictions), BUT is able to view the correct usage information for everyone else.

test25.testCaseDes: Test 25: This is a profile with a Primary member and 2 Adult Dependents. Both the Adult Dependents have PHI enabled and have NOT given access to Primary Enrollee. The Procedure Codes covered for this profiles are ONLY: D1110, D1120 and D4346. This test verifies that Primary is able to see his/her own usage information and is restricted by Omnibus Rules when viewing Dependents usage information. Dependents' PHI flags should have no effect on Primary's access to their information.

test26.testCaseDes: Test 26: This is a profile with a Primary member and 2 Adult Dependents. Both the Adult Dependents have PHI enabled. The Procedure Codes covered for this profiles are ONLY: D1110, D1120 and D4346. This test verifies that member 02 is NOT able to see his/her usage information (because of PHI restrictions). Member 02 should also be restricted by Omnibus Rules when viewing others' usage information in the plan. Member 03's PHI flags should have no effect on Member 02's access to his/her information (But will be restricted by Omnibus).
